{"TopicId":179430,"ForumId":44,"TopicTitle":"ISS Discussion Thread","CreatedByName":"NSEP","CreatedById":165635,"CreatedDateTime":"2018-10-31T11:13:10Z","PageNum":9,"Articles":[{"CreatedByName":"FleshJeb","CreatedById":111640,"CreatedDateTime":"2021-11-16T20:35:43Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00224055777\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022179430\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221637076990\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022208000\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022Beccab\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n4 hours ago, Beccab said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nAt what size does trackable become untrackable generally? 1 centimeter? 1 millimeter?\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nMaybe 0.3 cm, per this (which also has other useful information):\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsEmbeddedOther\u0022\u003E\n\u003Ciframe allowfullscreen=\u0022\u0022 data-controller=\u0022core.front.core.autosizeiframe\u0022 data-embedid=\u0022embed11506904\u0022 scrolling=\u0022no\u0022 src=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?app=core\u0026amp;module=system\u0026amp;controller=embed\u0026amp;url=https://twitter.com/torybruno/status/1460403960284516354\u0022 style=\u0022height:635px;\u0022\u003E\u003C/iframe\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"JoeSchmuckatelli","CreatedById":154477,"CreatedDateTime":"2021-11-16T20:49:08Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Ca contenteditable=\u0022false\u0022 data-ipshover=\u0022\u0022 data-ipshover-target=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?/profile/111640-fleshjeb/\u0026amp;do=hovercard\u0022 data-mentionid=\u0022111640\u0022 href=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?/profile/111640-fleshjeb/\u0022 rel=\u0022\u0022\u003E@FleshJeb\u003C/a\u003E Cool graphic!\u00A0 Thanks\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"FleshJeb","CreatedById":111640,"CreatedDateTime":"2021-11-16T21:08:08Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00224055923\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022179430\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221637095748\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022154477\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022JoeSchmuckatelli\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n17 minutes ago, JoeSchmuckatelli said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Ca contenteditable=\u0022false\u0022 data-ipshover=\u0022\u0022 data-ipshover-target=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?/profile/111640-fleshjeb/\u0026amp;do=hovercard\u0022 data-mentionid=\u0022111640\u0022 href=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?/profile/111640-fleshjeb/\u0022 rel=\u0022\u0022\u003E@FleshJeb\u003C/a\u003E Cool graphic!\u00A0 Thanks\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nThe alternative was to post something about Mark 48 ADCAPs and debris fields at the bottom of the Atlantic, but this is much more productive.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"StrandedonEarth","CreatedById":89439,"CreatedDateTime":"2021-11-16T22:21:49Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nOkay, I\u2019ll bite: how much propellant would be needed to raise the relevant part of the \u00A0ISS\u2019 orbit above the worst of the debris stream?\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nSmooth move, Russia. A way to weasel out of ISS participation ASAP?\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"sh1pman","CreatedById":147869,"CreatedDateTime":"2021-11-16T22:45:25Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00224055956\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022179430\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221637101309\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u002289439\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022StrandedonEarth\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n22 minutes ago, StrandedonEarth said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nOkay, I\u2019ll bite: how much propellant would be needed to raise the relevant part of the \u00A0ISS\u2019 orbit above the worst of the debris stream?\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nOne full Starship tanker.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00224055956\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022179430\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221637101309\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u002289439\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022StrandedonEarth\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n23 minutes ago, StrandedonEarth said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nSmooth move, Russia. A way to weasel out of ISS participation ASAP?\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nNot ASAP, debris will still need several years to reach as low as ISS orbit.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"mikegarrison","CreatedById":137807,"CreatedDateTime":"2021-11-16T22:51:17Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00224055963\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022179430\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221637102725\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022147869\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022sh1pman\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n5 minutes ago, sh1pman said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nOne full Starship tanker.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nNot ASAP, debris will still need several years to reach as low as ISS orbit.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nNot all debris will have the same velocity vector. Some bits may already have paths that cross the ISS altitudes.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"sh1pman","CreatedById":147869,"CreatedDateTime":"2021-11-16T22:59:11Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00224055965\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022179430\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221637103077\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022137807\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022mikegarrison\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n5 minutes ago, mikegarrison said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nNot all debris will have the same velocity vector. Some bits may already have paths that cross the ISS altitudes.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nMaybe, but no tracked pieces have such tracks yet, as far as I know. According to the press release by Russia MoD, the lowest-reaching debris are 40 km above ISS altitude. If this was intended as a way to weasel out of ISS, looks like they failed \u003Cspan\u003E\u003Cimg alt=\u0022:)\u0022 data-emoticon=\u0022\u0022 src=\u0022//kerbal-forum-uploads.s3.us-west-2.amazonaws.com/emoticons/default_k_smiley.gif\u0022 title=\u0022:)\u0022\u003E\u003C/span\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"tater","CreatedById":119411,"CreatedDateTime":"2021-11-16T23:29:38Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00224055965\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022179430\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221637103077\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022137807\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022mikegarrison\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n34 minutes ago, mikegarrison said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nNot all debris will have the same velocity vector. Some bits may already have paths that cross the ISS altitudes.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nYeah, this is very true, and skews towards smaller pieces... I want to say the radars get down to 2cm objects.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00224055967\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022179430\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221637103551\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022147869\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022sh1pman\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n27 minutes ago, sh1pman said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nMaybe, but no tracked pieces have such tracks yet, as far as I know. According to the press release by Russia MoD, the lowest-reaching debris are 40 km above ISS altitude. If this was intended as a way to weasel out of ISS, looks like they failed \u003Cspan\u003E\u003Cimg alt=\u0022:)\u0022 data-emoticon=\u0022\u0022 src=\u0022//kerbal-forum-uploads.s3.us-west-2.amazonaws.com/emoticons/default_k_smiley.gif\u0022 title=\u0022:)\u0022\u003E\u003C/span\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nThe large bits will get spotted first, and the smallest debris will never be detected unless it hits something. Conservation of momentum means that the smaller pieces can be given higher velocities\u2014and if retrograde, their orbits end up lower. So we would expect the debris most likely to hit ISS earlier (even if a very probability) to be those smallest, likely never detected pieces. Of course not being detectable ISS cannot maneuver to avoid them. Chances of a catastrophic hit are then much smaller, but small damage, leaks, etc are entirely possible.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"sh1pman","CreatedById":147869,"CreatedDateTime":"2021-11-16T23:48:24Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00224055978\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022179430\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221637105378\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022119411\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022tater\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n13 minutes ago, tater said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nThe large bits will get spotted first, and the smallest debris will never be detected unless it hits something. Conservation of momentum means that the smaller pieces can be given higher velocities\u2014and if retrograde, their orbits end up lower. So we would expect the debris most likely to hit ISS earlier (even if a very probability) to be those smallest, likely never detected pieces. Of course not being detectable ISS cannot maneuver to avoid them. Chances of a catastrophic hit are then much smaller, but small damage, leaks, etc are entirely possible.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nOf course, but I was responding to the part about \u201Cweaselling out of ISS\u201D. If the MoD says there\u2019s no danger, Roscosmos can\u2019t use the debris danger as an argument in favor of withdrawal from the program.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"tater","CreatedById":119411,"CreatedDateTime":"2021-11-17T00:01:43Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00224055987\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022179430\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221637106504\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022147869\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022sh1pman\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n13 minutes ago, sh1pman said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nOf course, but I was responding to the part about \u201Cweaselling out of ISS\u201D. If the MoD says there\u2019s no danger, Roscosmos can\u2019t use the debris danger as an argument in favor of withdrawal from the program.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nYeah, I was just talking about risk to ISS in general. Obviously over time the large bits will start crossing ISS as well as they decay over months/years.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"mikegarrison","CreatedById":137807,"CreatedDateTime":"2021-11-17T03:00:46Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00224055987\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022179430\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221637106504\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022147869\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022sh1pman\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n3 hours ago, sh1pman said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nOf course, but I was responding to the part about \u201Cweaselling out of ISS\u201D. If the MoD says there\u2019s no danger, Roscosmos can\u2019t use the debris danger as an argument in favor of withdrawal from the program.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u0022Weaseling out of the ISS\u0022 was a silly comment. If Russia wants out of the ISS, all they have to do is stop sending cosmonauts and resupply ships up there. It\u0027s not like anyone can force them to do it.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nHowever, I have about 0.00% trust in the Russian MoD being able to say that there is no risk to the ISS from this debris cloud that they just created for no good reason at all.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cspan class=\u0022ipsType_reset ipsType_medium ipsType_light\u0022 data-excludequote=\u0022\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cstrong\u003EEdited \u003Ctime datetime=\u00222021-11-17T03:01:20Z\u0022 title=\u002211/17/2021 03:01  AM\u0022 data-short=\u00222 yr\u0022\u003ENovember 17, 2021\u003C/time\u003E by mikegarrison\u003C/strong\u003E\n\u003C/span\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"tater","CreatedById":119411,"CreatedDateTime":"2021-11-17T03:20:20Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00224056043\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022179430\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221637118046\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022137807\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022mikegarrison\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n20 minutes ago, mikegarrison said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nHowever, I have about 0.00% trust in the Russian MoD being able to say that there is no risk to the ISS from this debris cloud that they just created for no good reason at all.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nLeft hand no knowing what the right is doing? It\u0027s really, really senseless.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"swjr-swis","CreatedById":152460,"CreatedDateTime":"2021-11-17T13:45:26Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00224055978\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022179430\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221637105378\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022119411\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022tater\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n14 hours ago, tater said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nChances of a catastrophic hit are then much smaller, but small damage, leaks, etc are entirely possible.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nNot to mention the increased risk to EVA astronauts, with an undetermined and non-trackable number of bullet-like objects flying by the station in the near future.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"sh1pman","CreatedById":147869,"CreatedDateTime":"2021-11-17T16:10:32Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00224056049\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022179430\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221637119220\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022119411\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022tater\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n12 hours ago, tater said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nLeft hand no knowing what the right is doing? It\u0027s really, really senseless.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nRoscosmos most likely knew, but couldn\u2019t do anything about it. They have no authority over MoD, and the launch was from the army base nearby to Plesetsk, not the cosmodrome itself.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"kerbiloid","CreatedById":129408,"CreatedDateTime":"2021-11-17T16:38:22Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nIf the sat was in a co-planar orbit, the relative speed would be lower than when its debris are on a cross-orbit.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nDoes the ISS keep some permanent orientation, or its rotation is chaotical?\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"cubinator","CreatedById":150330,"CreatedDateTime":"2021-11-17T17:25:36Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00224056346\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022179430\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221637167102\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022129408\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022kerbiloid\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n44 minutes ago, kerbiloid said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nDoes the ISS keep some permanent orientation, or its rotation is chaotical?\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nISS keeps one side facing the Earth most of the time. Like this:\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsSpoiler\u0022 data-ipsspoiler=\u0022\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsSpoiler_header\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cspan\u003ESpoiler\u003C/span\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsSpoiler_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Cimg alt=\u0022International Space Station - Wikipedia\u0022 data-ratio=\u002263.75\u0022 width=\u00221200\u0022 src=\u0022https://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/0/04/International_Space_Station_after_undocking_of_STS-132.jpg/1200px-International_Space_Station_after_undocking_of_STS-132.jpg\u0022\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nImagine the station moving out of the page towards you.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nSometimes they change the orientation if they need to dock something weird or have some other extraneous thing to do, but mostly it stays like this.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nAs for the orbital plane, the inclination always stays the same and the longitude precesses slowly due to Earth\u0027s oblateness.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"kerbiloid","CreatedById":129408,"CreatedDateTime":"2021-11-17T17:28:58Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00224056362\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022179430\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221637169936\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022150330\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022cubinator\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n7 minutes ago, cubinator said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nISS keeps one side facing the Earth most of the time.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nYes, but does it keep its orientation along the orbit.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI.e. are there permanently \u0022windward\u0022 and \u0022downwind\u0022 sides, relative to the new LEO meteor stream (delta-Tselinides)?\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Ca href=\u0022https://space.skyrocket.de/doc_sdat/tselina-d.htm\u0022 rel=\u0022external nofollow\u0022\u003Ehttps://space.skyrocket.de/doc_sdat/tselina-d.htm\u003C/a\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nSo, are there modules more dangerous than others?\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cspan class=\u0022ipsType_reset ipsType_medium ipsType_light\u0022 data-excludequote=\u0022\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cstrong\u003EEdited \u003Ctime datetime=\u00222021-11-17T17:32:09Z\u0022 title=\u002211/17/2021 05:32  PM\u0022 data-short=\u00222 yr\u0022\u003ENovember 17, 2021\u003C/time\u003E by kerbiloid\u003C/strong\u003E\n\u003C/span\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Beccab","CreatedById":208000,"CreatedDateTime":"2021-11-17T17:35:19Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00224056346\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022179430\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221637167102\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022129408\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022kerbiloid\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n57 minutes ago, kerbiloid said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nIf the sat was in a co-planar orbit, the relative speed would be lower than when its debris are on a cross-orbit.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nDoes the ISS keep some permanent orientation, or its rotation is chaotical?\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nIt depends on whether Nauka is docking or not\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"kerbiloid","CreatedById":129408,"CreatedDateTime":"2021-11-17T17:43:59Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00224056366\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022179430\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221637170519\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022208000\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022Beccab\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n7 minutes ago, Beccab said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nIt depends on whether Nauka is docking or not\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nIt\u0027s docked and nailed.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n***\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nSo, if there is a dangerous side, permanently facing the incoming delta-Tselinides, isn\u0027t it wise to delivere a bullet-protective screen, to put the station in meteor shadow?\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"tomf","CreatedById":57809,"CreatedDateTime":"2021-11-17T19:35:32Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00224056373\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022179430\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221637171039\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022129408\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022kerbiloid\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n1 hour ago, kerbiloid said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nIt\u0027s docked and nailed.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n***\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nSo, if there is a dangerous side, permanently facing the incoming delta-Tselinides, isn\u0027t it wise to delivere a bullet-protective screen, to put the station in meteor shadow?\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nLooks like it pretty much keeps the same orientation but with a 15 degree wobble in what they call the torque equilibrium attitude or TEA.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Ca href=\u0022https://www.forbes.com/sites/quora/2017/04/26/how-does-the-international-space-station-keep-its-orientation/?sh=17f52e433a18\u0022 rel=\u0022external nofollow\u0022\u003Ehttps://www.forbes.com/sites/quora/2017/04/26/how-does-the-international-space-station-keep-its-orientation/?sh=17f52e433a18\u003C/a\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"SSTO Crasher","CreatedById":215483,"CreatedDateTime":"2021-11-18T15:57:49Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nAs you have probably already heard, Russia has tested a weapon on one of their own satellites, putting the crew of the ISS in danger and polluting space with hundreds of new peaces of junk. As \u003Ca contenteditable=\u0022false\u0022 data-ipshover=\u0022\u0022 data-ipshover-target=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?/profile/159036-matt-lowne/\u0026amp;do=hovercard\u0022 data-mentionid=\u0022159036\u0022 href=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?/profile/159036-matt-lowne/\u0022 rel=\u0022\u0022\u003E@Matt Lowne\u003C/a\u003E\u00A0says, we need to protect the space dolphins and space polar bears, and of coarse the space humans\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"JoeSchmuckatelli","CreatedById":154477,"CreatedDateTime":"2021-11-18T17:11:48Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00224056724\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022205655\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221637251069\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022215483\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022SSTO Crasher\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n1 hour ago, \u003Cabbr title=\u0022Single Stage to Orbit\u0022\u003ESSTO\u003C/abbr\u003E Crasher said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nAs you have probably already heard, Russia has tested a weapon on one of their own satellites, putting the crew of the ISS in danger and polluting space with hundreds of new peaces of junk. As \u003Ca contenteditable=\u0022false\u0022 data-ipshover=\u0022\u0022 data-ipshover-target=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?/profile/159036-matt-lowne/\u0026amp;do=hovercard\u0022 data-mentionid=\u0022159036\u0022 href=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?/profile/159036-matt-lowne/\u0022 rel=\u0022\u0022\u003E@Matt Lowne\u003C/a\u003E\u00A0says, we need to protect the space dolphins and space polar bears, and of coarse the space humans\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nStart reading here:\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Ciframe allowfullscreen=\u0022\u0022 data-controller=\u0022core.front.core.autosizeiframe\u0022 data-embedauthorid=\u0022119411\u0022 data-embedcontent=\u0022\u0022 data-embedid=\u0022embed5495032398\u0022 scrolling=\u0022no\u0022 src=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?/topic/179430-iss-discussion-thread/\u0026amp;do=embed\u0026amp;comment=4055321\u0026amp;embedComment=4055321\u0026amp;embedDo=findComment\u0022 style=\u0022height:222px;max-width:502px;\u0022\u003E\u003C/iframe\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nOdd - that was to Tater\u0027s post on this - recalculating\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\\\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Ciframe allowfullscreen=\u0022\u0022 data-controller=\u0022core.front.core.autosizeiframe\u0022 data-embedauthorid=\u0022119411\u0022 data-embedcontent=\u0022\u0022 data-embedid=\u0022embed9690436970\u0022 scrolling=\u0022no\u0022 src=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?/topic/179430-iss-discussion-thread/\u0026amp;do=embed\u0026amp;comment=4055321\u0026amp;embedComment=4055321\u0026amp;embedDo=findComment\u0022 style=\u0022height:222px;max-width:502px;\u0022\u003E\u003C/iframe\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nRecalculating\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Ciframe allowfullscreen=\u0022\u0022 data-controller=\u0022core.front.core.autosizeiframe\u0022 data-embedauthorid=\u0022165635\u0022 data-embedcontent=\u0022\u0022 data-embedid=\u0022embed7076143928\u0022 scrolling=\u0022no\u0022 src=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?/topic/179430-iss-discussion-thread/page/7/\u0026amp;do=embed\u0022 style=\u0022height:197px;max-width:502px;\u0022\u003E\u003C/iframe\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cspan class=\u0022ipsType_reset ipsType_medium ipsType_light\u0022 data-excludequote=\u0022\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cstrong\u003EEdited \u003Ctime datetime=\u00222021-11-18T17:15:49Z\u0022 title=\u002211/18/2021 05:15  PM\u0022 data-short=\u00222 yr\u0022\u003ENovember 18, 2021\u003C/time\u003E by JoeSchmuckatelli\u003C/strong\u003E\n\u003C/span\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"AHHans","CreatedById":197939,"CreatedDateTime":"2021-11-19T14:03:39Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nThe following popped up in my youtube suggestions. It\u0027s the communication between Huston (and/or SpaceX) and the ISS during the recent event when the ISS crew had to shelter from the debris cloud:\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsEmbeddedVideo\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv\u003E\n\u003Ciframe allowfullscreen=\u0022\u0022 frameborder=\u00220\u0022 height=\u0022113\u0022 width=\u0022200\u0022 data-embed-src=\u0022https://www.youtube.com/embed/Mc4dL5oeSrs?feature=oembed\u0022\u003E\u003C/iframe\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"RCgothic","CreatedById":132560,"CreatedDateTime":"2021-11-19T17:01:39Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00224055967\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022179430\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221637103551\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022147869\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022sh1pman\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\nOn 11/16/2021 at 10:59 PM, sh1pman said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nMaybe, but no tracked pieces have such tracks yet, as far as I know. According to the press release by Russia MoD, the lowest-reaching debris are 40 km above ISS altitude. If this was intended as a way to weasel out of ISS, looks like they failed \u003Cspan\u003E\u003Cimg alt=\u0022:)\u0022 data-emoticon=\u0022\u0022 src=\u0022//kerbal-forum-uploads.s3.us-west-2.amazonaws.com/emoticons/default_k_smiley.gif\u0022 title=\u0022:)\u0022\u003E\u003C/span\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nThe MoD release is incorrect. According to LEOLab\u0027s Gabbard chart, at least 11 items with perigees below the altitude of the ISS (~410km) have already been detected.\u003Cimg alt=\u00221*wApWuAMjjfRsVrRI6WDZDA.png\u0022 class=\u0022ipsImage\u0022 data-ratio=\u002281.38\u0022 height=\u0022673\u0022 width=\u0022827\u0022 src=\u0022https://miro.medium.com/max/2450/1*wApWuAMjjfRsVrRI6WDZDA.png\u0022\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nThey estimate 5-10x more smaller objects than this, which because smaller objects can be imparted with more retrograde velocity, many of those will also have low perigees.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nSo there are already probably a hundred new debris items crossing the ISS\u0027s orbit.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nFurthermore, orbital decay will eventually bring all of these ~1500-2500 objects down through the ISS\u0027s orbit.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nAlmost all of these will be untrackable, and because the target was in a polar orbit orbital precession will eventually shape the debris field into a complete sphere. So there will be no advance warning of hazards, no possibility of manoeuvring to avoid the debris field, and no specific times in the ISS\u0027s orbit where additional precautions can be taken.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nIt\u0027s just a risk the station (and any others soon to launch) just have to live with from now on.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nA spectacularly reckless and ill-conceived test.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"tater","CreatedById":119411,"CreatedDateTime":"2021-11-20T02:51:16Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsEmbeddedOther\u0022\u003E\n\u003Ciframe allowfullscreen=\u0022\u0022 data-controller=\u0022core.front.core.autosizeiframe\u0022 data-embedid=\u0022embed3411111072\u0022 scrolling=\u0022no\u0022 src=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?app=core\u0026amp;module=system\u0026amp;controller=embed\u0026amp;url=https://twitter.com/SpaceNav2/status/1461870939012931585?s=20\u0022 style=\u0022height:730px;\u0022\u003E\u003C/iframe\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00224057208\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022179430\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221637341299\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022132560\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022RCgothic\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n9 hours ago, RCgothic said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nA spectacularly reckless and ill-conceived test.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nExcept breaking stuff was the point. Not reckless, I think malicious.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"}]}